<br>
Here is the ezboard policy that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>must</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be adhered to.  These are the things that are non-negotiable in order for us to use this board.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>USER CONDUCT <br>
You agree to not use the Service to: <br>
<br>
(a) violate or solicit the violation of any applicable local, state, national or international law; <br>
<br>
(b) infringe the rights of any third party, including but not limited to intellectual property rights and privacy or publicity rights <br>
<br>
(c) upload, post, email or otherwise transmit any Content that <br>
<br>
        (1) is unlawful, threatening, abusive, tortious, defamatory, obscene, libelous, or invasive of another's privacy; <br>
<br>
        (2) consists of instructional information on illegal activities, including, but not limited to, hacking, cracking, and phreaking; <br>
<br>
        (3) violates or infringes in any way upon the proprietary rights of others, including, without limitation, copyrighted software, music, photographs, text, videos or artwork; <br>
<br>
        (4) constitutes pornography, or sexual material of an obscene nature or that violates local, state or national laws; <br>
<br>
        (5) is the private information of another such as their addresses, phone number, Social Security number or credit card number; <br>
<br>
        (6) contains software viruses, Trojan horses or any other computer code, files or programs designed to interrupt, destroy or limit the functionality of any computer software or hardware or telecommunications equipment; or <br>
<br>
        (7) you do not have a right to upload or post due to contractual or other legal obligation.<br>
<br>
(d) impersonate any person or entity, including, but not limited to, an ezboard official, forum leader, guide or host, or falsely state or otherwise misrepresent your affiliation with a person or entity; <br>
<br>
(e) forge headers or otherwise manipulate identifiers in order to disguise the origin of any Content transmitted through the Service;<br>
<br>
(f) interfere with or disrupt the Service, computer servers or boards accessible through the Service; <br>
<br>
(g) disseminate off-topic messages on boards promoting any product, service, web site, board or venture, or promote boards on the Service through unsolicited electronic mail messages to third parties. <br>
<br>
If you do use the Service to commit any of the above, ezboard may, at its sole discretion. terminate your password, account (or any part of it) or ability to use the Service, and remove and discard any Content within the Service. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think we should add mm's suggestion to the policy as well...<br>
<br>
mm has come up with an excellent idea for dealing with things like this. In chat last night she suggested that we move this sort of thing to the Black Hole and then start a discussion (set to sticky) in the forum that the problem took place in. Put a link to the thread in question in the discussion, then we let the members decide what do with the thread. <br>
<br>
The options would be to.. <br>
<br>
a) Delete the offending post(s) and move it back <br>
b) Move it back and leave it as is<br>
c) edit the post(s) and move it back<br>
d) Move it to the Abyss<br>
e) Leave the thread in the Black Hole.<br>
<br>
This should apply to flamers and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>blatant</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spammers.  We're talking ten posts in a row type stuff that is meant only to annoy.<br>
<br>
If a thread is started with spam (ie repetitive and/or trolling and annoying) and only spam comments follow with no chance of having a topic, then it may be moved immediately to the Black Hole.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I also want to add the code of conducts for the Moderators and Administrators<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Mod/Admin policies<br>
<br>
<br>
Moderator Restrictions<br>
1. No moderator may warn outside his or her forum. <br>
2. No moderator may delete a thread.<br>
3. No moderator may lock a thread.<br>
4. A moderator may NOT edit or delete a post unless it contains a image that violates ezboard policy, a image that stretches a thread out of shape, contains a members real life information, (ie: phone number, address, credit card number, etc) or by consent of the members of this board.<br>
<br>
(All moderator rules also apply to Administrators with the exception of rule 1.)<br>
<br>
Administrative Restrictions<br>
<br>
1. No Admin. may ban someone unless all other admins agree - unless someone is an immediate threat to the board (ie: a porn spammer). As soon as the majority of admits is online that ban must be gone over and decided whether or not to be lifted. <br>
2. No Permabans <br>
3. All Bans must be listed publicly as they occur (with reason for the ban listed). <br>
4. No admin. may make changes to the board without consent of the other admins. <br>
5. All admin. must abide by the decisions of the membership on all issues. <br>
<br>
<br>
Moderators and Administrators are subject to all the same rules and consequences as the membership. If a ban is warranted in the case of either a Moderator or an Administrator that person will also immediately lose his job on this board.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Number 4 in the moderator list could use a little work I think...  Something short and a little more specific probably.<br>
<br>
Number 5 on the Admin list also needs some clarification and discussion.<br>
