Last post from a thread moved to BH<br>
<br>
Lady Meanoiche<br>
<br>
 The problem with not editing is that a lot of old Slipstreamers can be a little sensitive, sometimes overly so. To some extent this might be in part due to the tendency of the admins there to treat us like babies but whatever the reason it means that a lot of people might not be comfortable with a board where hardly any editing is done at all.<br>
<br>
I think it really depends on the individual case. We need to consider what happens if people repeatedly ask for something to be edited or deleted? Will the mods/admins be able to bow to the will of the people? And don't forget that the staff of this board will still be a part of the board. The point being is that we should be aiming to create as much freedom as possible for everyone.<br>
<br>
If someone's posting shit and people are annoyed about it it's not wise to go so far to protect the freedom of the person posting shit that you ignore the freedom of everyone else.  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Also I think its a bad idea to just ban people out of the blue. Without a warning system thats pretty much what happens. If you aren't going to have warnings I don't think you should have bans.<br>
<br>
